<HEAD>President Ill, Will Go to United States</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SAN SALVADOR, El Salvador (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Jose Napoleon Duarte
will travel to the United States early this week for diagnosis and
treatment of a serious stomach problem, his spokeswoman said Sunday.
   Duarte, 62, was diagnosed here late last week as suffering from
a bleeding ulcer, spokeswoman Ana Maria Ruiz said in a telephone
interview.
