<1ST_LINE>d a AM-BRF--FreezerAccident     05-29 0123</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Freezer Accident,0124</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Woman Killed When Freezer Falls on Her</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CLOVIS, N.M. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A woman listening to records in her living
room was killed by a freezer that fell on top of her after it was
pushed through the wall by her husband's out-of-control car, police
said.
   Ora Lee Byrd, 68, died instantly in the freak accident Saturday,
they said.
   Her husband, Joe, was parking the car when his foot slipped off
the brake and hit the accelerator. The car went through the garage
door, hit a freezer kept inside the garage and propelled it through
the wall, police said.
   The freezer fell on Mrs. Byrd, who was sitting on a couch on the
other side of the wall, police said.
</TEXT>
